de-applicatie-signalen-kent-verscheidene:
The Signals application has several roles. 
In the settings screen it is possible to adjust the rights per role. 
This includes only reading rights, changing statuses, adding a note or being able to use the THOR button. 
Changes to a role will apply to all users with that role.
de-applicatie-signalen-maakt-gebruik-van:
The Signals application uses departments. 
It is possible to set which subcategories can be viewed per department. 
By giving a department access to a subcategory, all employees assigned to these relevant departments can see all notifications in this subcategory. 
In addition, it is possible to make a department responsible for a specific subcategory. 
If a department is responsible for a specific subcategory, this is visible on the detail page, the department in question is then shown in brackets next to the subcategory. 
The role of responsibility is also used in the monthly reports. 
Assigning this responsibility automatically results in access being granted to this subcategory.

een-melding-in-signalen-wordt-automatisc:
A notification in Signals is automatically assigned to a main category by the machine learning tool. 
In this settings page it is possible to adjust the display on the public maps per main category. 
The visibility of the main category on the map can be set. 
The public name and icon can be changed. 
For the notification card you can indicate whether the subcategories of the main category should be visible in the filter menu.

elke-melding-in-de-applicatie-signalen-w:
Each notification in the Signals application is assigned to a subcategory when created by a machine learning tool. 
Each subcategory has a description, which is only used for internal use. 
The service promise that belongs to the subcategory assigned by the machine learning tool is used in feedback to the reporter. 
Once a notification is in the application, it is possible to adjust the subcategory. 
The handling period in weeks or working days is not fed back to the reporter, which is intended to internally manage the handling of reports. 
In this settings page it is possible to adjust the data per subcategory.

om-toegang-te-krijgen-tot-de-applicatie-:
To gain access to the Signals application, it is necessary that an employee has been added, whereby the email address is the same as the login account. 
The password cannot be changed in this settings screen. 
Each user must be assigned a role and a department, this combination ensures the correct rights. 
It is not possible to give an employee rights in this settings screen to create or maintain users, this so-called super role can only be created in Django by the functional manager.
